Tunisian Men Openly Admit Cheating

One out of five men in Tunisia said they’ve cheated on their previous partners. There are two explanations for that everyday cheating. Firstly, they really did, and secondly, it’s the most common who cheated on their previous partners.

1 in 5 Tunisians thinks it is acceptable to cheat on their partner. 80% of those who think that way are women. There’s also another very strange statistic. 91% of media users also think benefitting from another woman’s body is acceptable behavior!

1 in 5 Tunisians Believes Women Should Give Up their Career for a Man

The Tunisian society has always encouraged men to work as they’d never look at women’s career as a real job. In fact, the researchers made the research during 2014 and 2015, and things didn’t really change since the market economic situation is deplorable. One on twenty men said that women should stay home and look after the kids.
